    <text id="B0309T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell quotes from a Circular stating the need to restrict the political
                    activity of agents while they are representatives of the Bureau.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs.</abbr> 9th Sub <abbr
                            expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> John W.
                            Jordan<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >A.S.A.Comr.</abbr> 4th <abbr expan="Division">Div.</abbr><lb/>Staunton,
                            <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-04-28">
                            <abbr expan="April 28, 1868">April 28/68</abbr>
                        </date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The following extract from a communication received from Head Quarters Assistant
                    Commissioner District of Virginia, is furnished for your information and
                    guidance, viz:</p>

                <p>"It is not thought advisable that Bureau Officers or Agents should attend
                    political Conventions.</p>

                <p>"While it is clearly their duty to advise the freedmen in regard to their civil
                    and political rights under the Laws of Congress, it is not deemed proper that
                    officers or agents should become political partisans."</p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient Servant">Obedt
                        St</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
